        "formula": "Let X be input tensor of shape (N, C, L) with N=64, C=192, L=65536. Let K=8 (kernel_size), S=1 (stride), P=4 (padding), D=3 (dilation). Define padded tensor X_pad of shape (N, C, L+2P) such that X_pad[n,c,i] = X[n,c,i-P] if P ≤ i < L+P else -∞. Then for n ∈ [0,N), c ∈ [0,C), o ∈ [0,L_out) where L_out = floor((L + 2P - D*(K-1) - 1)/S + 1) = 65523, the output Y is computed as: Y[n,c,o] = max_{k=0}^{K-1} X_pad[n,c, o*S + k*D].",
        "boundary_treatment": "Padding: P=4 padded by -∞ on both sides along L dimension. For indices i < P or i ≥ L+P in X_pad, value is -∞, so max ignores those positions. Output length L_out computed by floor((L + 2P - D*(K-1) - 1)/S + 1). Stride S=1, dilation D=3. No explicit masking needed; the -∞ padding handles out-of-bound window elements.",
